      "id": "vulnerability--b6e268fa-125a-4517-80ab-55e3d7b0918e",
      "name": "React2Shell",
      "description": "React2Shell is a critical vulnerability (CVE-2025-55182) in React Server Components versions 19.0.0, 19.1.0, 19.1.1, and 19.2.0. It allows remote code execution via unsafe deserialization of user-supplied data using the React 'Flight' protocol. Attackers can send a single malicious HTTP request to gain control over server-side code execution without authentication. The flaw impacts frameworks such as Next.js and has been widely exploited.",
      "created": "2025-12-03T00:00:00Z",
      "external_references": [
        {
          "source_name": "CVE",
